EC2-3 (SonarQube Server - Ubuntu)

1. Update the Server
apt update = Refresh the package list
apt upgrade = Install available updates

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

2. Install Docker

sudo apt install docker.io -y
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
newgrp docker

3. Verify Docker

docker --version
docker ps

4. Create Docker Network

docker network create sonarnet

5. Run PostgreSQL Container

docker run -d \
--name postgres \
--network sonarnet \
-e POSTGRES_USER=sonar \
-e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=sonar123 \
-e POSTGRES_DB=sonar \
-v postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data \
postgres:15

Verify:

docker ps

6. Run SonarQube Container

docker run -d \
--name sonarqube \
--network sonarnet \
-p 9000:9000 \
-e SONAR_JDBC_URL=jdbc:postgresql://postgres:5432/sonar \
-e SONAR_JDBC_USERNAME=sonar \
-e SONAR_JDBC_PASSWORD=sonar123 \
-v sonarqube_data:/opt/sonarqube/data \
-v sonarqube_extensions:/opt/sonarqube/extensions \
sonarqube:lts-community

7. Verify Containers

docker ps

8. Access SonarQube

http://<EC2-Public-IP>:9000

Default Login

Username: admin
Password: admin

9. Configure Security Group

Allow inbound:
TCP 9000 → Your IP (for browser access)
or
TCP 9000 → Jenkins Security Group (recommended)

10. Jenkins Configuration

- Install SonarScanner on the Jenkins Agent (EC2-2).
- Login to SonarQube.
- Go to Administration → Security → Users → Tokens.
- Generate a token.
- In Jenkins:
  - Manage Jenkins → Plugins → Install "SonarQube Scanner".
  - Manage Jenkins → System → Add SonarQube Server.
    - Name: SonarQube
    - Server URL: http://<EC2-3-Private-IP>:9000
    - Authentication Token: Add the generated token as a Jenkins Credential.
  - Manage Jenkins → Tools → Configure SonarScanner.

11. Jenkins Pipeline

For SonarScanner CLI:

withSonarQubeEnv('SonarQube') {
    sh 'sonar-scanner'
}

For Maven Projects:

withSonarQubeEnv('SonarQube') {
    sh 'mvn sonar:sonar'
}

Important Notes

- Install SonarQube Server only on EC2-3.
- Install SonarScanner only on the Jenkins Agent (EC2-2).
- Jenkins Agent must be able to reach EC2-3 on TCP port 9000.
